description.plain:
K/DA is an animated girl-group by League of Legends to promote a line of character cosmetics. It originally featured vocals from four of the game’s most recognizable females: Ahri, Akali, Evelynn, and Kai'Sa.

The group’s name is an acronym for “Kills, Deaths, and Assists,” an in-game feature that measures a player’s performance in a League match.

The group premiered at the League of Legends 2018 World Championship in Incheon, South Korea with their debut single, “POP/STARS.” Like the game’s Pentakill before them, the girl group’s success prompted the release of additional music, like their ALL OUT EP in 2020. The group also played a hand in debuting League of Legends' 152nd champion, Seraphine.

The band even has a page dedicated to their music on the League of Legends Universe.

description.plain:
Ascend the throne. K/DA is back with “MORE,” their second single released in 2020, ahead of their debut EP, ALL OUT.

It’s the first single to feature guest vocals from collaborator Seraphine, voiced by Chinese singer-songwriter Lexie Liu. Seraphine also made her League of Legends debut on October 13, 2020. The original lineup from the massively successful debut single “POP/STARS” sees a return as well, with Madison Beer, SOYEON and MIYEON of (G)I-DLE, and Jaira Burns.

description.plain:
“VILLAIN” is the third track from K/DA’s ALL OUT EP. The song serves as Evelynn’s feature track with vocals from both German-American singer Kim Petras and Madison Beer, who previously voiced Evelynn on both “POP/STARS” and “MORE.”

The song was first teased on October 10th, 2020.
